{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01RW9YP1H7oMYEgwJYWZ6Xyp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have everything. Let me write the F30 plan.\n\nKey observations:\n1. F29 was already approved and created ALL the files: `src/lib/generator.ts`, all 4 route files, and tests.\n2. F30's description says \"Implement GET /api/generate/[job_id]/status SSE, POST cancel, and GET /api/generate/jobs routes\" — but all 3 of these routes already exist from F29.\n3. The F29 plan explicitly listed these files as CREATE, and the eval confirmed them all passing.\n\n\n4. So F30 is essentially a no-op from an implementation perspective — everything was already built in F29. I should write the plan honestly, noting that these files already exist from F29 and that F30's work is to verify correctness of the existing routes and potentially add any missing test coverage specific to these three route handlers.\n\nLet me check the spec sections more carefully to see if there's anything the existing routes might be missing. Looking at the GET /api/generate/[job_id]/status SSE endpoint, the spec requires streaming progress events with a specific format, and the existing implementation already polls every 500ms, emits data events, and closes on terminal states.\n\nComparing the spec examples against what's implemented, the running events include throughput and eta_seconds while complete events have elapsed_ms — and the existing code matches this exactly. The POST /api/generate/[job_id]/cancel endpoint sets a cancellation flag checked between batches and returns the right response format, and the GET /api/generate/jobs endpoint lists recent jobs with status and row counts as specified. All three routes are fully implemented, so F30 should focus on verification and test coverage rather than new implementation work. The SSE route handles terminal states like failed and cancelled using the same non-complete payload format with throughput and eta_seconds, which aligns with the spec since it doesn't specify separate formats for those states. I notice the error field from JobState isn't included in failed status payloads, but since the spec doesn't require it, I'll leave it as is.\n\nNow I'm reconsidering how to frame F30 in the plan — even though F29 already created these files, F30 should describe the target state based on the spec requirements for these three routes, and I'll note in the dependencies that the implementation already exists from the previous feature.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":398,"cache_read_input_tokens":59554,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":398},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ad37df17-7a83-47f0-993e-b421b8843c55","uuid":"8f646f52-b6ce-4b3b-9d33-a1fa5a443e3f"}
